race.comment: SMOOTH REASON (2) made it two wins and a minor placing from her last three starts when she scored by 8 metres on November 1 over 2090m at Hobart. No excuses from this advantageous draw. Tackles a similar assignment and she can go right on with the job. TULLAH GIRL (1) found form and scored two runs back then came back to earth when she broke and finished fifth last start over 2180m at Burnie, coming home 21 metres from the winner. Will enjoy a nice run from this favourable starting position. Needs to get it right to beat this field but she is up to the job. GLENVIEW LANIKAI (5) has been thereabouts of late and is a great chance to break through. Good effort last time out when she finished third at this track over 2200m. HARBOUR SPRINGS (3) is in the mix following a fourth at her most recent appearance over 1720m at Penrith.
